results.name: Supreme Hole Punch Denim Blue
results.title: Vans Sk8-Hi Supreme Hole Punch Denim Blue
results.description:
The Vans Sk8-Hi Supreme Hole Punch Denim Blue is a special edition of the classic Vans silhouette released in part of a collaborative effort between Vans and popular streetwear brand Supreme.

The Vans Hole Punch Denim Blue is a high-top skating shoe constructed from a mix of suede and denim material and features a blue and black colorways with accents of white. The blue covers the side panels of the shoe and incorporates a rugged design while black covers the heel area and eyestays extending to the toe box. Other unique design elements on the shoe include a padded collar and the classic Vans side stripe while branding elements include ‘Supreme’ text on the heel a Vans logo on the tongue and Vans x Supreme collaborative logo under the heel area.

The Vans Sk8-Hi Supreme Hole Punch Denim Blue was released for retail on 9th July 2020 priced at $110.

results.name: Supreme Hole Punch Denim Blue
results.title: Vans Slip-On Supreme Hole Punch Denim Blue
results.description: The Vans Slip On Supreme Hole Punch Denim Blue is a stylish and comfortable shoe that is perfect for everyday wear. The shoe features a denim blue colorway with a hole punch design that adds a unique touch to the classic slip-on silhouette. The upper is made of durable denim material that is both breathable and lightweight, making it ideal for warmer weather. The shoe also features a padded collar and footbed for added comfort, as well as a rubber outsole that provides excellent traction and durability. The Vans Slip On Supreme Hole Punch Denim Blue was released on July 9th, 2020, and retails for $98. Something we love about the Vans Slip On Supreme Hole Punch Denim Blue is its versatile design that can be dressed up or down. What our experts think as best features are the unique hole punch design and the comfortable padded collar and footbed. What we love about the Vans Slip On Supreme Hole Punch Denim Blue is its combination of style and comfort. The standout feature of the Vans Slip On Supreme Hole Punch Denim Blue is its unique hole punch design that adds a touch of personality to the classic slip-on silhouette. Our experts especially love the durable denim material and the rubber outsole that provides excellent traction and durability.

results.name: Supreme Hole Punch Denim Black
results.title: Vans Slip-On Supreme Hole Punch Denim Black
results.description:
The Vans Slip-On Supreme Hole Punch Denim Black is part of a collaboration between Vans and Supreme, an American fashion label known for its skateboarding aesthetic.

This skateboarding shoe features the classic Vans Slip-On silhouette with a hole punch pattern across the upper. Instead of looking like clean-cut holes, each hole punch puncture is frayed and creates a tear in the denim. The fraying along the edges gives the shoes a DIY feel. While the upper is made of black denim, the midsole comes in a bright white rubber. Like other Vans Slip-On models, this model has an outsole made of vulcanized rubbed with a waffle pattern. This cross-crossed, waffle pattern increases traction on a variety of surfaces, including cement and pavement.

Something our experts at StockX like about this sneaker is the dual Supreme and Vans branding that appears on the midsole. The Vans Slip-On Supreme Hole Punch Denim Black was released on July 9th, 2020, and retailed at $98.

results.name: Supreme Hole Punch Denim Black
results.title: Vans Sk8-Hi Supreme Hole Punch Denim Black
results.description:
As part of a longstanding partnership between Vans and Supreme, the two companies dropped the Sk8 Hi Hole Punch Denim Black. As the name suggests, denim is one of the primary components of the Sk8 Hi Hole Punch sneaker, and the uppers include layers of soft yet durable material. Additional lettering is present on the tongue of the Sk8 Hi silhouette.

The Vans Sk8 Hi Supreme Hole Punch Denim released in July 2020 and retailed for $110.

results.name: Supreme Skull Pile (Green)
results.title: Vans Sk8-Hi Supreme Skull Pile (Green)
results.description: The Vans Sk8-Hi Supreme Skull Pile Green is a must own pair If you gotta stay fly-y-y-y, y-y, y-y, y. Made in collaboration with Supreme as part of a larger "Skull Pile" Pack, these Vans draw inspiration from Three 6 Mafia’s Juicy J and his infamous green skull tee look from the Stay Fly video. One of three colorways that dropped alongside each other, this pair comes in black and true white, and sports a classic black/white color scheme with a green "skull pile" graphic throughout. Originally dropping in March of 2018, these are a must own for anyone looking to tear da club up.

results.name: Supreme Jean Paul Gaultier Burgundy
results.title: Vans Era Supreme Jean Paul Gaultier Burgundy
results.description:
The Vans Era Supreme Jean Paul Gaultier Burgundy is a shoe designed as a collaboration between Vans, Supreme, and iconic designer Jean Paul Gaultier.

This version of the Vans Era is made with a durable canvas upper. The forefoot appears in a deep green color with a floral pattern around the toe. Burgundy appears around the seams connecting the forefoot to the middle panel of the shoe, while floral patterns with roses appear on each side underneath the ankle. Burgundy again appears around the seams connecting this section to the heel, which features the same floral pattern. A Vans tag appears at the seam between the forefoot and middle panel on the lateral side, and the shoe sits atop a thick black rubber midsole. A red Vans Off The Wall panel appears on the heel.

Our favorite thing about this sneaker is the rose patterning that appears on each section of the shoe. The Vans Era Supreme Jean Paul Gaultier Burgundy was released on April 11, 2019, and retailed for $108.

results.name: Supreme Fuck the World Black
results.title: Vans Sk8-Hi Supreme Fuck the World Black
results.description:
The Vans Sk8-Hi Supreme Fuck the World Black combines Vans heritage design with Supreme style in this collaboration between the sneaker company and the streetwear brand.

This high-top Supreme x Vans skate sneaker features an upper that builds upon a base of black canvas with a padded collar. Black suede overlays adorn the heel counter as well as the eyestays and the vamp. A black leather strip ripples across the side panel. White deco stitching courses across the base as well as the overlays. White flat laces crisscross over the black canvas tongue, which features a white tongue tag branded with Fuck the World in black. The inner side of this tongue tag sports Supreme branding. White and black foxing leads to textured white side walls that feature a red license plate with dual branding.

Our favorite detail of this pair of sneakers is the colorful Fuck the World branding on the outer ankle of each shoe. The Vans Sk8-Hi Supreme Fuck the World Black was released on October 10, 2019, for $85 retail.

results.name: Supreme Jean Paul Gaultier Peach
results.title: Vans Era Supreme Jean Paul Gaultier Peach
results.description:
Vans has teamed up with streetwear brand Supreme and celebrated fashion designer Jean Paul Gulatier to bring a unique and distinctive aesthetic to their classic skate shoe with the introduction of the Vans Era Supreme Jean Paul Gaultier Peach.

The Vans Era is an iconic silhouette that has maintained its popularity since its introduction in the late 1970s. It is crafted with a sturdy canvas upper that is breathable and lightweight, yet also durable, and uses metal eyelets to house its dynamic lacing system. A padded collar enhances comfort around the ankle, while a low-tip design allows for greater freedom of movement. A signature waffle-patterned outsole delivers quality traction on and off the skateboard, and the brand’s "Off the Wall" logo can be seen on the heel and tongue.

What our experts love most about the Vans Era Supreme Jean Paul Gaultier Peach is the two-toned color blocking and lush floral patterning that Gaultier brings to their aesthetic in a light nod to his penchant for punk influences. These shoes retailed for $108 when they first released on April 11, 2019.

results.name: Supreme Diamond Plate Black
results.title: Vans Sk8-Hi Supreme Diamond Plate Black
results.description:
The Vans Sk8-Hi Supreme Diamond Plate Black, a collaboration between Vans and the Supreme skate and streetwear brand, reimagines a classic 1978 Vans silhouette to create this high-octane skate shoe.

The Supreme x Vans Sk8-Hi Diamond Plate Black features an upper of black and white canvas decorated with shapes inspired by industrial-themed slip-resistant steel plating. Black suede overlays cover the toebox, eyestays, and heel, providing enhanced support for this skating high-top. An undulating strip of white leather courses across the side panel and matches the flat white laces. The white vulcanized midsole rests on a gum rubber outsole with crosshatch tread for providing traction on the board.

One of the most delightful aspects of this sneaker are the hits of branding. Supreme branding appears in red on the license plate, blue on the side panel, and black on the interior tongue tag. The exterior tongue tag sports dual branding. The Vans Sk8-Hi Supreme Diamond Plate Black was released on May 9, 2019, or $110 retail.

results.name: Supreme Black
results.title: Vans Sid Pro Supreme Black
results.description:
The Vans Sid Pro Supreme Black takes a retro Vans silhouette that was originally launched in the ’90s and reimagines it in collaboration with the New York–based streetwear label, Supreme.

This iteration of the Vans Sid Pro silhouette features an upper crafted from black suede. Deco stitching in white courses across the upper, outlining the heel counter, collar, and eyestays. Flat black laces cross over a black suede tongue. The sock liner is white leather and matches a flying Vans logo embroidered on the side panel. The vulcanized sole unit features white side walls with black striping and a red license plate with dual branding. The gum rubber outsole is designed for grip.

The standout detail on this streamlined pair of kicks is the Supreme branding on the tongue. Embroidered in white, the brand is in Old English, giving the sneaker definite panache. The Vans Sid Pro Supreme Black was released on October 4, 2018, for $110 retail.
